column11: In 1862, Brooklyn Catholics raised a cross over their first church, a 20-by-30 foot building that later doubled in size thanks to an addition. The building also served as a Catholic school. A larger church was constructed 11 years later in 1883,|but was destroyed in a gas explosion in August 1911. a visiting priest rushed inside to save the Blessed Sacrament. He later crawled out of the church with his clothes burned off and his skin scorched. 1910 postmark.
